Interface Pairing

All Superinterfaces:
BinaryOperation, PathExpression
All Known Implementing Classes:
PairingImpl
public interface Pairing
extends BinaryOperation

Pairing takes as input two functions f and g, such that def(f)= def(g),
and returns a function f ^ g: def(f) -> range(f) x range(g),
deﬁned by: (f ^ g)(x)= (f(x), g(x)) , for all x in def(f).
